hot_days=(Mashad_df['Tmax']>20).sum()

hot_days=(Mashad_df['Tmax']>20).sum()
cold_days=(Mashad_df['Tmin']<10).sum()

# autopact

hot_days=(Mashad_df['Tmax']>20).sum()
cold_days=(Mashad_df['Tmin']<10).sum()
normal_days =((Mashad_df['Tave']>10) & (Mashad_df['Tave']<15)).sum()
mylist=[hot_days, cold_days, normal_days]
# make a pie chart for us 
colors=['yellow', 'blue', 'Green']
myexplode = [0,0,0.2]
plt.figure(figsize=(5, 5))

plt.pie(mylist, labels=['Hot', 'Cold', 'Normal'], colors=colors, startangle=20, explode = myexplode, shadow=True, autopct='%1.1f')
#autopct='%1.1f'  show the value with 1 decimal place, but not as a percent, just the raw number.
#autopct='%1.1f%%'  show the value as a percentage with 1 decimal place (the extra % at the end is

plt.title('Temperature distribution')
plt.show()
